View:"Bali's tourism scene is centered around the southern part of the island, where the beaches and towns offer something for everyone. Kuta is a hotspot for lively party enthusiasts, Canggu caters to the trendy hipster crowd, Ubud draws in yoga enthusiasts, Seminyak appeals to the wealthy and stylish, and Nusa Dua is ideal for those seeking luxurious all-inclusive 5-star resorts. This wide range of options makes Bali an effortless choice for a peaceful and enjoyable vacation.",featured:!0,qna:[{question:"Day 1: Arrival in Bali | Uluwatu Kecak Dance & Dinner at Jimbaran (5 hrs)",answer:"Upon arrival at Ngurah Rai Airport in Bali, you will meet our representative and be transferred directly to your hotel. Your first stop will be the stunning Uluwatu Temple, perched 100 meters above the ocean on a cliff, offering breathtaking views. While at the temple, enjoy the captivating Kecak Dance, performed by around 50 singers. This unique dance is one of the few that relies solely on vocals, with a history that dates back to pre-instrumental Bali. After the performance, a short drive will take you to Jimbaran Bay, where you can indulge in a delicious seafood dinner at a cozy seaside restaurant."},{question:"Day 2:Water Sports at Tanjung Beach | Balinese Spa (2 hrs) | Sunset Tanah Lot Tour",answer:"Start your day with exciting water sports at Tanjung Beach, including a Banana Boat Ride, Flying Fish, and Jet Ski for a thrilling adventure on the water. Afterward, unwind with a relaxing 2-hour Balinese Spa treatment, where traditional Balinese healing techniques will leave you feeling refreshed and rejuvenated. Following your spa experience, enjoy a transfer to your Pool Villa for a peaceful retreat. Pick-up time: 08:00 AM from your hotel in South Bali or Ubud."},{question:"Day 3 : Ubud Kintamani Tour with Waterfall Visit",answer:"Enjoy a full-day private tour, starting with a 09:00 AM pick-up from your hotel in South Bali or Ubud. The first stop will be Celuk Village, where you can explore Bali’s renowned gold and silver craftsmanship. Afterward, head to Mas Village, known for its traditional woodcarvings, showcasing the intricate artistry of local craftsmen. Next, visit the Ubud Art Market, where you can shop for unique souvenirs and Balinese artwork. Then, immerse yourself in the lush beauty of Tegallalang Rice Terrace, one of Bali's most iconic landscapes, famous for its stunning terraced fields. Afterward, enjoy the natural beauty of Tegenungan Waterfall, a peaceful spot perfect for photos and relaxation. Continue your journey to Kintamani for a breathtaking view of Mount Batur and Lake Batur, offering a serene atmosphere and magnificent scenery. Finally, conclude your tour with a visit to a coffee plantation, where you can learn about Bali’s coffee culture and sample various local varieties, including the famous Luwak coffee. This private tour offers a rich blend of culture, nature, and local experiences, all tailored to your pace."},{question:"Day 4 : Full-Day Besakih Temple & Tenganan Tour (10 hrs)",answer:"Begin your 10-hour tour with a 09:00 AM pick-up from your hotel in South Bali or Ubud. First, visit Besakih Temple on Mount Agung, the Mother Temple of Bali, offering stunning views and spiritual significance. En route, stop at Celuk Village for gold and silver crafts, Kerta Gosa in Klungkung to see historical courthouse murals, and Goa Lawah, the sacred bat cave. Finally, explore Tenganan Village, a Bali Aga village famous for its traditional gringsing weaving. This tour offers a blend of culture, history, and spirituality."},{question:"Day 5 : Transfer to your Pool Villa and enjoy a beachside candlelight dinner.",answer:"After breakfast, transfer to your Pool Villa. In the evening, enjoy a romantic candlelight dinner."},{question:"Day 6 : Depart at the appropriate time for your onward journey.",answer:"After breakfast at the hotel, check out and depart for the airport at the appropriate time for your return flight."}],packageI